title: Polarized-protons scattering by even-mass germanium and selenium isotopes at 22-MeV incident energy.

x4freetext: .Correction in author` list has been done,
The germanium and selenium targets in form of
isotopically enriched material evaporated onto a carbon
foil of thickness 25-mug/cm**2 were used. The average
target thickness was about 200-mug/cm**2. The isotope
interest was enriched to over 90% in Ge-72, Ge-74,
Se-78 and Se-80, to about 85% in Ge-70 and Se-76 and
-By authors. The experiments were designed to obtain
an accuracy of 3% in two-photon levels.
It was not possible, however, to achieve this in all
Because of the presence of the unwanted isotopes in per
cent amounts in our targets authors started the
analysis of the elastic peaks by determining the values
of the normalization and the optical-model parameters
as if the data contained no contributions from isotopic
impurities. Then the experimental data were corrected
using the data from the other targets and the procedure
was iterated a few times until the normalization
factors became stable. Normalization of the inelastic
scattering data was also derived from this procedure.
